text:
Value buying / generating alpha from PE expansion is a very short lived process and needs skill in terms of timing entrry and exit as well.

All that is not required when you are buying companies that grow fast. Even buying them at high PE, the E of P/E increases at such good pace or the consistency and guarantee of future stable cash flow is so strong that the PE keeps on falling and price increases to reflect the previous high PE.
Examples of such companies are Nestle.
